Package executor.service.holder

Class ScenarioQueueHolder

java.lang.Object
executor.service.holder.ScenarioQueueHolder
All Implemented Interfaces:
QueueHolder<Scenario>
@Component public class ScenarioQueueHolder extends Object implements QueueHolder<Scenario>
Implementation of QueueHolder for managing a queue of Scenario instances.

The ScenarioQueueHolder class serves as a concrete implementation of the QueueHolder interface. It is annotated with Component, indicating that it is a Spring-managed bean and can be injected into other components. The underlying queue implementation is a LinkedBlockingQueue, suitable for managing scenarios in a concurrent environment.

This class provides access to a blocking queue of Scenario instances through the getQueue() method. The scenarios are held in a BlockingQueue, which is well-suited for scenarios where multiple threads may be producing and consuming scenarios concurrently.

Ensure proper configuration and usage of this class within the application to manage scenarios effectively. The usage of a blocking queue provides thread-safety and efficient handling of scenarios in a multi-threaded environment.

    • getQueue

      public BlockingQueue<Scenario> getQueue()
      Gets the blocking queue of Scenario instances.

      This method is responsible for providing access to the underlying blocking queue of Scenario instances. The blocking queue, represented by the scenarios field, is initialized with a LinkedBlockingQueue, making it suitable for concurrent scenarios where multiple threads may be producing and consuming scenarios.

      It is important to note that the returned queue instance may be safely used in a multi-threaded environment due to the inherent thread-safety provided by the LinkedBlockingQueue implementation.

      Specified by:
